# Ownership & Cascade Analysis

Think end-to-end: Who else is affected? Ensure whole system stays consistent.

Found one instance of a bug or anti-pattern? Search for similar issues elsewhere (Grep).

**When fixing, check:**
- Similar patterns elsewhere?
- Will fix affect other components? (imports/references)
- Symptom of deeper architectural issue?
- Should pattern be abstracted for reuse?

Don't fix immediate issue only — fix the **class** of issues when appropriate.

If root cause is in a shared component, analyze and fix all consumers affected by the same flaw.

Complete full investigation cycle before marking done.
